Installations

Download and install JAVA Development Kit (JDK)  
Download and install Eclipse (or whatever IDE you prefer)  https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
Install TestNG and the Eclipse testNG plugin (follow instructions on the page) https://testng.org/doc/download.html
Download webdrivers using links at the bottom of this page,  https://selenium.dev/projects/
Download and install git for windows  https://gitforwindows.org/

Eclipse project configuration

Download and install Eclipse https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
Using Eclipse interface to generate an ssh-key pair  https://vzurczak2.wordpress.com/2012/07/13/creer-des-cles-ssh-avec-eclipse/
Add your public key into your gitlab account
Via Eclipse, import a new project from git
Import from URL
Copy URL git@gitlab.com:votreLienUrl.git
Import only master branch
Import as general project
Right click on project -> Convert to maven project
Copy paste your drivers locations in config.yaml
Docker and selenium installation
Install docker https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/debian/ then do this  https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/linux-postinstall/
Git clone this project https://github.com/SeleniumHQ/docker-selenium

Tools documentations
Java, https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/
Selenium, https://selenium.dev/documentation/en/
Maven, https://maven.apache.org/guides/index.html
TestNG, https://testng.org/doc/documentation-main.html
Eclipse, https://help.eclipse.org/2018-12/index.jsp?topic=/org.eclipse.mat.ui.help/welcome.html
Git, https://git-scm.com/docs
